SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 11b: Form 990 Review Process
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COPIES OF THE 990 ARE MADE AVAILABLE TO THE GOVERNING BOARD FOR DISCUSSION AND ACCEPTANCE PRIOR TO FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 12c: Explanation of Monitoring and Enforcement of Conflicts
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ANNUALLY, THE INTERNATIONAL AGRI-CENTER BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND EX-OFFICIO DIRECTORS SIGN A CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY. THE DIRECTORS ARE REQUIRED TO DISCLOSE ANY CONFLICT OF INTEREST AND NOT PARTICIPATE IN THE BOARD MEETING FOR THE ENTIRE TIME THE MATTER IS DISCUSSED AND VOTED UPON.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 15b: Compensation Review and Approval Process for Officers and Key Employees
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION HAS THEIR PERSONNEL COMMITTEE EVALUATE AND MAKE RECOMMENDATIONS REGARDING COMPENSATION WHICH ARE THEN EITHER APPROVED, MODIFIED OR DENIED BY THE ENTIRE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 19: Other Organization Documents Publicly Available
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CONDENSED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE PUBLISHED IN THE ORGANIZATION NEWSLETTER. COMPLETE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND OTHER GOVERNING DOCUMENTS ARE MADE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST IN THE ORGANIZATIONS CORPORATE OFFICE.
